Data type specifies the type of value a variable holds. This is required in programming to do various operations without causing an error.

It is not necessary to specify the type in Python because the Python interpreter automatically interprets the variable type.

type() – With this function we can verify which type of data type is used in a variable.

Following are the types of Data Types

1.Numeric

    Integer

    Complex number

    Float

2.Dictionary

3.Boolean

4.Set

5.Sequence Type

    String

    List

    Tuple
